The paper deals with image and video processing, specifically frame interpolation, which is a common task in computer vision and graphics. The use of optical flow and feature pyramids also suggests a focus on computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves differentiable image sampling, which falls under the category of graphics (cs.GR). The use of deep learning models for synthesis and fine-tuning suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.MM and cs.LG). Finally, the paper proposes a novel method for handling conflicts in mapping multiple pixels to the same target location, which could be considered a contribution to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
